979
01:19:52,115 --> 01:19:53,741
So don't worry about it too much.

980
01:19:53,825 --> 01:19:56,244
Do you think they're really
waiting for their dad?

981
01:19:56,911 --> 01:19:58,538
Do you think that's why they're here?

982
01:19:58,913 --> 01:20:00,540
We should've split up at the beginning.

983
01:20:01,124 --> 01:20:03,334
Then we just ended up hurting the kids.

984
01:20:05,336 --> 01:20:07,964
Jimmy, Tommy, open the door!

985
01:20:08,047 --> 01:20:10,174
You know there's no other way!

986
01:20:10,216 --> 01:20:12,468
You think it's just the kids getting hurt?

987
01:20:12,552 --> 01:20:14,554
Do I look like someone who never gets hurt?

988
01:20:14,637 --> 01:20:16,556
Who asked you to get hurt?

989
01:20:17,849 --> 01:20:18,766
You could've given up at the beginning

990
01:20:18,850 --> 01:20:20,560
if you didn't think you could handle it!

991
01:20:21,728 --> 01:20:23,062
What made you stay?

992
01:20:24,230 --> 01:20:25,690
Just so you could have a peace of mind?

993
01:20:28,735 --> 01:20:30,278
Peace of mind?

994
01:20:32,739 --> 01:20:35,867
Then are you running away
for your peace of mind?

995
01:20:35,950 --> 01:20:37,702
I did my best for our family!

996
01:20:37,744 --> 01:20:38,995
I didn't run away like you,

997
01:20:39,078 --> 01:20:43,374
and tried to the point where
I'm not ashamed of myself.

998
01:20:43,458 --> 01:20:46,294
Anything I could do for our family, I...

999
01:20:51,883 --> 01:20:53,301
Tell me, June.

1000
01:20:54,677 --> 01:20:56,804
What makes us a family?

1001
01:21:06,773 --> 01:21:12,820
Do I need to say that in words?

1002
01:21:23,247 --> 01:21:24,874
Don't fight.

1003
01:23:07,393 --> 01:23:10,897
Good! Good!
My neck!

1004
01:23:12,064 --> 01:23:14,942
Oh my God!
You must be so worried!

1005
01:23:16,110 --> 01:23:19,447
Chun-seop!
What a bad man he is!

1006
01:23:20,615 --> 01:23:22,241
He just wanted the contract.

1007
01:23:22,325 --> 01:23:24,660
I didn't know what was going on.

1008
01:23:26,829 --> 01:23:31,667
Again, I'm never forcing
you to go to Korea.

1009
01:23:33,336 --> 01:23:36,255
But!

1010
01:23:36,339 --> 01:23:37,965
Let's think about this together.

1011
01:23:38,758 --> 01:23:40,885
Next year you'll be an adult.

1012
01:23:40,927 --> 01:23:42,553
You can bring your family to Korea.

1013
01:23:42,637 --> 01:23:45,389
But imagine not having any money!

1014
01:23:45,431 --> 01:23:47,475
Or a home!
How would that be?

1015
01:23:47,558 --> 01:23:49,477
Think siblings will be happy?

1016
01:23:54,649 --> 01:23:59,195
June, I really wanna help you.

1017
01:23:59,278 --> 01:24:02,198
But! There's nothing
I can do here.

1018
01:24:02,281 --> 01:24:05,701
I can only help you in Korea.
Trust me!

1019
01:24:07,954 --> 01:24:10,289
Okay?
Trust me! Okay?

1020
01:24:10,665 --> 01:24:12,124
A year max,

1021
01:24:12,166 --> 01:24:14,252
and your world will be
completely different.

1022
01:24:14,293 --> 01:24:16,337
A new world!

1023
01:24:17,505 --> 01:24:18,839
Then after that,

1024
01:24:18,923 --> 01:24:20,132
you can always bring your siblings...

1025
01:24:20,216 --> 01:24:22,552
- Do I...
- Do I what?

1026
01:24:22,635 --> 01:24:24,345
